page.title: 12PARR ENGINEERING
page.content:
We parked the car by Whites Garage and then we made our way to Parr Engineering and we went inside the office and we saw Mr P. Wright. He gave us some glasses to protect our eyes.
Mr Wright took us to the store room where materials are kept.They showed us some nuts and bolts. Then we looked at a robot which punched holes in a sheet of metal which worked on a {computer.}Then he showed us another robot which can cut through 8 inches of thick metal.
Later we saw a big oven which baked the paint. Parr Engineering make {tractor cabs and metal sheds}for the {B.B.C.}and{air venting ducts}which they export to{Singapore, Egypt and {Libya.
